title.rendered: Delhi vs UP, India Women’s League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Delhi: Meg Lanning (c), Shafali Verma, Marizanne Kapp, Jemimah Rodrigues, Alice Capsey, Jess Jonassen, Taniya Bhatia (wk), Arundhati Reddy, Shikha Pandey, Radha Yadav, Tara Norris

UP: Alyssa Healy (c & wk), Shweta Sehrawat, Kiran Navgire, Tahlia McGrath, Deepti Sharma, Grace Harris, Simran Shaikh, Devika Vaidya, Sophie Ecclestone, Anjali Sarvani, Rajeshwari Gayakwad

Pitch Report

Venue: Dr DY Patil Sports Academy, Mumbai

(Based on last two matches)

Pitch Type: Good for batting

1st innings average score: 188

2nd innings average score: 120

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 50%

Batting 2nd: 50%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Sophie Ecclestone hasn’t gone wicketless in the format for seven consecutive games, bagging four three-fors in the process.

Kiran Navgire thrives under pressure. She has two fifties in three matches across the 2022 Women’s Challenger and this tournament.

Meg Lanning’s 72 off 43 in the last game did not come as a surprise. She likes scoring big in India, hitting 601 runs at an average of 74 in 15 competitive T20s.

Marizanne Kapp featured in the Best11 in the last five matches, while Shafali Verma and Shikha Pandey had 60% success.

In her 10-game young T20 career, Tara G Norris has a staggering strike rate of 11.8 with the ball.

Alyssa Healy has generated the 30-run bonus in five of the last eight matches, aggregating 288 runs at a stunning average of 48 during this period.

Deepti Sharma went wicketless in only two of the last 10 games. In addition, bowlers failed to dismiss her in three of the six matches she batted.

Spinners have picked up 54% wickets in the last two games at the venue.
